        "body": "<!-- ⚠️⚠️ Do Not Delete This! feature_request_template ⚠️⚠️ -->\n<!-- Please read our Rules of Conduct: https://opensource.microsoft.com/codeofconduct/ -->\n<!-- Please search existing issues to avoid creating duplicates. -->\n\n<!-- Describe the feature you'd like. -->\n#  Refactor: Improve SidebarPart Layout Synchronization & Activity Bar Consistency\n\n## Summary\nThis pull request refactors and modernizes the `SidebarPart` implementation to significantly enhance the consistency, reliability, and visual stability of the Activity Bar and Sidebar across all configurations.  \nThe changes address long standing issues related to update ordering, layout synchronization, and visibility handling resulting in smoother, more predictable Workbench behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Key Improvements\n- **Instant Activity Bar synchronization**  \n  Layout changes (visibility, position, badge updates) now propagate immediately and reliably.\n- **Stronger hidden/visible state management**  \n  Consolidates logic to prevent flicker, redundant layout passes, and mismatched state transitions.\n- **Refined CompositeBar positioning pipeline**  \n  Ensures accurate placement and reflow of viewlet icons across TOP, BOTTOM, and TITLE positions.\n- **Optimized layout and border logic**  \n  Simplifies `updateStyles()`, improves alignment, and removes unnecessary recomputation.\n- **Improved structure and readability**  \n  Introduces clearer boundaries, consistent naming, and deterministic update sequencing for better long-term maintainability.\n\n---\n\n## Why This Change?\nThe Sidebar and Activity Bar interact dynamically across several modes.  \nUnder rapid transitions such as switching Activity Bar positions, moving the Sidebar, toggling visibility, or applying theme changes previous behavior could cause:\n\n- Noticeable layout jitter  \n- Delayed or missed synchronization updates  \n- Inconsistent border rendering  \n- Redundant or out of order layout calls  \n\nThis refactor introduces a stable and predictable update flow, greatly improving overall UI smoothness and reliability.\n\n---\n\n## Testing\nThe refactor was thoroughly validated across multiple UI and configuration combinations:\n\n- Activity Bar visibility toggles update instantly  \n- Sidebar left ↔ right moves preserve correct CompositeBar alignment  \n- Theme changes reapply border/layout rules without flicker  \n- All viewlets activate and display correctly under every Activity Bar mode  \n- Tested with custom themes, experimental features, and various workbench states  \n\nThis PR is:\n\n- Fully backward compatible  \n- Non breaking  \n- Without API changes  \n- Safe for all extensions  \n\n---\n\n## Final Note\nThis PR is intentionally focused, well scoped, and aligned with existing Workbench patterns.  \nI welcome feedback and am happy to incorporate any improvements the maintainers suggest.\n\nThank you very much for reviewing this contribution.\n",
